name: $alternate
desc: The code should no longer be used, but was used in the past.

name: $deprecated
desc: The code is an alternative to be used when a case insensitive code is required (when the primary codes are case sensitive).

name: $case-insensitive
desc: The code is an alternative to be used when a case sensitive code is required (when the primary codes are case insensitive).

name: $case-sensitive
desc: The code is an alternative for the primary code that is built using the expression grammar defined by the code system.
